707612f-b.text:
(1)
First Avenue, east side, from 46th to 48th Streets, showing a filling and service station from 46th to 47th Streets, where nine old five story tenement houses, 826-42 First Avenue, used to stand. Behind the service station are old buildings belonging to Wilson & Company, packers; part of the Wilson slaughter house is shown
on the S.E. corner of 46th Street.
July 3, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same. First Avenue at N.E. corner of 46th Street. Many filling
stations and garages on First Avenue in the I92O's.
July 3rd,I934
P.L.Sperr,
No Reproductions.
(3)The same,showing East Side of First Avenue,45th to 46th Street.
September 28th,I940
P.L.Sperr,.

707610f-a.text:
First Avenue, east side, north across East 46th Street. In the foreground is a semi-open frontage extending from 46th to 47th Street's. Note the meat smoking house to the rear of same. The Beekman Towers (left) dominates
this locale.
July 23, 1939
September 28, 1940
P. L. Sperr
